SIMPLE: luculent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Luculent
<hw>Lu"cu*lent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>luculentus</ets>, from <ets>lux</ets>, <ets>lucis</ets>,
light.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lucid; clear; transparent.</def>
<rj><au>Thomson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Clear; evident; luminous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ Most
<xex>luculent</xex> testimonies.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Bright; shining in beauty.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Most debonair and <qex>luculent</qex> lady.</q> <rj><qau>B.
Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Luculently</ent>⟦br⟧
